    "narrative": "The Austin Waves offense is anchored today by **Gunnar Henderson** (81.88) and **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** (73.66), both of whom benefit significantly from facing S. Burke and McGreevy, respectively. **Gunnar Henderson** remains our highest-ceiling asset, as his leadoff spot and favorable dynamic platoon split against Burke provide the ideal environment for high R and HR output. Similarly, **Jackson Merrill** (70.99) is a core start; beyond his strong 70.99 efficiency, he is a primary target in our SB-scarcity strategy, as Keller\u2019s slow delivery significantly increases his likelihood of capitalizing on the basepaths today. **Kyle Tucker** (64.17) and **Josh Lowe** (62.54) also offer strong value, with **Josh Lowe** specifically benefiting from a +14% boost due to favorable platoon matchups that mitigate the risks of lower-order batting.\n\nOur most difficult decision centered on **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (48.73), who ultimately occupied our primary bench slot. While his underlying xwOBA of 0.384 is elite, the sheer difficulty of facing Ohtani\u2014who sports a 2.67 xERA\u2014crushed his efficiency score, pushing him behind the higher-upside profiles of **Jacob Wilson** (54.58) and **Nolan Schanuel** (54.42). We remain cautious regarding **Luis Robert Jr.** (49.50) and **Andy Pages** (49.32); while they hold starting spots, their respective platoon disadvantages and difficult pairings against R. Nelson and Cease leave them at the absolute floor of our recommended lineup. We are monitoring **Liam Hicks** (50.18) and **Drake Baldwin** (46.72) closely, as their scores are highly sensitive to the outcome of these SP matchups, and we have depth in **Coby Mayo** or **Miguel Vargas** if defensive replacements or late-lineup shifts occur.",
